==English==
===Noun===
'''larynx''' (''plural'' [[larynges]], larynxes)

#An organ of the neck of mammals involved in breath control, protection of the [[trachea]] and sound production, housing the vocal cords, and that is situated at the point where the upper tract splits into the trachea and the [[esophagus]].

